You are a Verilog-A hardware modeling expert. Below is a reference code snippet:
```
`include "discipline.h"
`include "constants.h"

// $Date: 1997/08/28 05:54:37 $
// $Revision: 1.1 $
//
//
// Based on the OVI Verilog-A Language Reference Manual, version 1.0 1996
//
//



//--------------------
// decimator
//
// -  decimator
//
// vin:		[V,A]
// vout:	[V,A]
// vclk:	[V,A]
//
// INSTANCE parameters
//    N          = oversampling ratio [V]
//    vtrans_clk = transition voltage of the clock [V]
//    tdel,trise,tfall = {usual} [s]
//
// MODEL parameters
//    {none}
//
// Produces a cumlative average of 'N' samples of 'vin'. 'vin' is sampled
// on the positive 'vclk' transition. The cumlative average of the previous
// set of 'N' samples is outputted until a new set of 'N' samples has been
// captured.
//
// Transfer Function:	1/N * (1 - Z^-N)/(1-Z^-1)
//
(* instrument_module *)
module decimator(vin, vout, vclk);
input vin,vclk;
output vout;
electrical vin, vout, vclk;
parameter integer N=64 from [0:inf); 
parameter real vtrans_clk=2.5;
parameter real tdel = 0 from [0:inf);
parameter real trise = 0 from [0:inf);
parameter real tfall = 0 from [0:inf);

   integer count;
   real sum;
   real vout_val;

   analog begin
      @ (cross(V(vclk) - vtrans_clk, 1.0)) begin
         sum = sum + V(vin);
         count= count + 1;

         if (count == N) begin
            count = 0;
	    vout_val = sum/N;
	    sum = 0.0;
         end
      end
      V(vout) <+ transition(vout_val,tdel,trise,tfall);
   end
endmodule
```
 Please correct the code based on the input error code, paying attention to functional and syntactic accuracy.

corrected code：
parameter integer N=64 from [0:inf);

 Correction Criteria：Changing N to real type with non-integer value (64.5) causes the integer counter 'count' to never equal N in the reset condition (count == N). This prevents the output from ever updating since the reset logic never triggers.

